com.google.cloud.resourcemanager

Class Policy

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.cloud.IamPolicy<String>
      • com.google.cloud.resourcemanager.Policy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public final class Policy
extends IamPolicy<String>
    An Identity and Access Management (IAM) policy for a project. IAM policies are used to specify access settings for Cloud Platform resources. A policy is a map of bindings. A binding assigns a set of identities to a role, where the identities can be user accounts, Google groups, Google domains, and service accounts. A role is a named list of permissions defined by IAM. Policies set at the project level control access both to the project and to resources associated with the project.
